<br>
This is what you need to do:<br>
<br>
1. Gather up to 10 players, yourself included<br>
2. Draw up a charter describing the guild's intentions and planned role.<br>
3. Start EQ and click Chat to connect to the chat server (all new members should do this).<br>
4. Leader types "#makeguild" to create a private chat channel.<br>
5. Type in a name for the channel that is similar to guild name and setup a password.<br>
6. Click "Create"<br>
7. Give the name and password to all prospective guild members.<br>
8. Tell all players to click on the private chat channel and enter the password.<br>
9. Once all players are in the channel, tell all players to type "#guildapprove"<br>
10. Type in "#makeguild" again to display the guild creation screen.<br>
11. Type in a summary of the charter (the guild's goals), the press "Finish."<br>
<br>
Your guild appears in the list as "Submitted."<br>
<br>
Wait for GM to review and determine if your charter should be editted.<br>
<br>
Once the guild is approved, you'll receive an email with further instructions (make sure your email address in your account information is accurate).<br>
<br>
Last step is to petition a GM between 2pm and 11pm PST to complet guild creation.<br>
<br>
...or, you could find an existing guild who could really use the numbers of people you can bring to the guild<br>
<br>
:)<br>
<br>
Good luck friend<br>
